"filemon" - simple program reading from file and show 
some information in system tray. It's possible to set 
interval beween readings (update interval) to decrease 
cpu usage and power consuption. 

Also it takes as arguments:
	1) Font color.
	2) Ending string (can be append to the end of the information).
	3) Title label (will be shown when cursor cover the icon).
	4) Number of bytes to read from file.

Only file is mandatory argument, another arguments have own default values.
